Re: I have a question about the Yoon and Dakuten/Handakuten
by Ongakuka » Sat 12.17.2011 7:42 am Someone said that you don't have to memorize the Yoon and Dakuten/Handakuten characters in Hiragana and Katakana.I think they probably meant it doesn't require any 'extra learning.' Which in a sense is true. For example, if you know all characters like 'ha hi hu he ho' become 'ba bi bu be bo' simply by adding the dakuten, it's not like you need to learn any 'new' characters or anything.Edit: changed handakuten to dakuten as it should have been.
Last edited by Ongakuka on Sun 12.18.2011 9:32 am, edited 1 time in total.
なぜなら、おまえは・・・・・・人形だ
